Informatics 102 Portfolio

This is my Info 102 class website, where I will be keeping a compilation of almost all the works I do in class.

Here's a picture of my dog!

View post on imgur.com
About me

Hey, I'm Drew Scott! I'm currently a student at the University of Washington. This website is meant to act as a portfolio or culmination of my work in the Informatics 101 class. I plan to graduate with a B.S. in Electrical Engineering in Fall of 2018. After that I hope to build really cool technology, if I could work on circuit boards for tanks that would be ideal. Some of my current hobbies include artisan crafts such as metalworking and woodworking. I also really enjoy rock climbing, hiking, pretty much anything outdoors! Thanks for reading, I hope you enjoyed it!

Currently I am not only working on getting the website up and running but also working on my group and I's project, which is to build an Emergency Response App into phones so that the process of coming to a person in need of help can be facilitated more efficiently.
